Semantic Document Retriever
A robust document retrieval system that uses Semantic Search to find relevant information within documents based on meaning rather than just keyword matching. Built using the RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) framework.

🚀 Overview
Unlike traditional search engines that look for exact word matches, this tool understands the context and intent behind a query. It processes documents through a specialized pipeline: Load, Embed, Store, and Retrieve.

🛠️ Features
Contextual Understanding: Uses advanced embeddings to capture the semantic meaning of text.

Scalable Vector Storage: Utilizes ChromaDB for efficient storage and fast similarity searches.

Flexible Integration: Built with LangChain for easy management of the AI workflow.

Accurate Retrieval: Designed to serve as the "brain" for AI agents or chatbots to query private datasets.

🏗️ The Pipeline
The project follows a standard four-stage architecture:

Load: Ingesting raw documents (PDFs, Text, etc.).

Embed: Converting text into high-dimensional numerical vectors using embedding models.

Store: Saving these vectors in a Vector Database (ChromaDB).

Retrieve: Querying the database to find the most mathematically similar document chunks to the user's input.
